{{Infobox power station | name = Hirono Power Station | name_official = 広野火力発電所 | image = Hirono Thermal Power Plant 05.jpg | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Japan | location_map_size = | location_map_caption= | coordinates = {{coord|37|14|18|N|141|01|04|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | country = Japan | location = [[Hirono, Fukushima]] | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = April 1980 | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = [[Tokyo Electric Power Company|Tepco]] | operator = | th_fuel_primary = [[Fuel oil]], [[Crude oil]] | th_fuel_secondary = [[Coal]] | th_fuel_tertiary = | ps_units_operational= 5 | ps_units_manu_model = | th_cogeneration = | th_combined_cycle = | ps_electrical_capacity= 4,400 MW | ps_electrical_cap_fac= | website = | extra = }}
{{Nihongo|'''Hirono Power Station'''|広野火力発電所|Hirono karyokuhatsudensho}} is an [[fossil-fuel power station]] located about 3&nbsp;km north of [[Hirono, Fukushima]], Japan.
The plant has an installed capacity of 4,400&nbsp;[[Megawatt|MW]]. Power is generated by three 600&nbsp;MW units, and two 1,000&nbsp;MW units. Units 1 to 4 run on [[fuel oil]] and [[crude oil]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://doc.research-and-analytics.csfb.com/docView?language=ENG&source=ulg&format=PDF&document_id=870328091&serialid=PiRN49RlTxHnoUCXED6hxZshdHN6kaG%2BFMWfw8TOAv8%3D#page=6 |title=Utilities Sector |author=Yuji Nishiyama |date=22 March 2011 |work= |publisher=Credit Suisse |accessdate=2 May 2011}}</ref> whereas unit 5 (600 MW) runs on coal.<ref>{{cite journal | author1 = Hiromasa Momma | author2 = Junichi Ishiguro | author3 = Takayuki Suto | author4 = Toshihiro Miyawaki | author5 = Ryuji Iwamoto | author6 = Tsuyoshi Nakahara | date = October 2004 | title = Commencement of the Commercial Operation of 600 MW Unit, "Hirono No. 5 Thermal Power Station of The Tokyo Electric Power Co., Inc." | journal = Mitsubishi Heavy Industries Technical Review | volume = 41 | issue = 5 | pages = 264–267 | publisher = Mitsubishi Heavy Industries | url = https://www.mhi.co.jp/en/technology/review/abstracte-41-5-264.html }}</ref> A new 600 MW coal-fired unit, Unit 6, commenced commercial operation in December, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/press/corp-com/release/2013/1232692_5130.html|website=TEPCO|accessdate=10 July 2014}}</ref>
The power plant located directly at the [[Pacific Ocean]] was damaged by the [[2011 Tōhoku earthquake and tsunami]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/torikumi/thermal/popup_01.html#s01 |title=Restoration of devastated thermal power station |author=Tepco |accessdate=2013-01-26}}</ref> [[Tokyo Electric Power Company|Tepco]] managed to return the first block to operation in July 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/tokyo-electric-starts-no-1-unit-at-hirono-thermal-power-station.html |title=Tokyo Electric Starts No. 1 Unit at Hirono Thermal-Power Station |author=Tsuyoshi Inajima |date=2011-07-04 |publisher=Bloomberg.com |accessdate=2013-01-26}}</ref>
