The '''Pawan Danavi Wind Farm''' (also internally known as the '''Kalpitiya Wind Farm''', and '''LTL Holdings Wind Farm''' after its parent company) is a {{Nowrap|10.2 [[Megawatt|MW]]}} onshore [[wind farm]] located near [[Kalpitiya]], in the [[Puttalam District]] of [[Sri Lanka]]. The wind farm utilizes twelve of {{Nowrap|[[Gamesa Corporación Tecnológica|Gamesa]]'s G58-850 kW}} [[wind turbine]]s. Pawan Danavi is a subsidiary company of {{Nowrap|LTL Holdings}}.<ref name=LBO>{{cite news|title=Sri Lanka wind power firm buys Gamesa turbines|url=http://www.lankabusinessonline.com/news/sri-lanka-wind-power-firm-buys-gamesa-turbines/1762518303|accessdate=20 February 2015|publisher=[[Lanka Business Online]]|date=16 June 2011}}</ref><ref name=DailyFT>{{cite news|title=Gamesa’s Indian unit strikes deal to supply wind turbines in Sri Lanka|url=http://www.ft.lk/2011/06/17/gamesa%E2%80%99s-indian-unit-strikes-deal-to-supply-wind-turbines-in-sri-lanka/|accessdate=20 February 2015|publisher=Daily FT|date=17 June 2011}}</ref><ref name=SundayTimes>{{cite news|title=Pawan Danavi to add 10.2 MW wind to SL in 2011|url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/110626/BusinessTimes/bt20.html|accessdate=20 February 2015|publisher=[[Sunday Times (Sri Lanka)|Sunday Times]]|date=26 June 2011}}</ref><ref name=WorldBank>{{cite web|title=Project Information - LTL Pawan Danavi Wind Farm|url=http://ppi-re.worldbank.org/data/project/ltl-pawan-danavi-wind-farm-6373|publisher=[[World Bank]]|accessdate=20 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=TheIsland>{{cite news|title=Gamesa’s Indian unit to supply wind turbines in Sri Lanka|url=http://www.island.lk/index.php?page_cat=article-details&page=article-details&code_title=27926|accessdate=20 February 2015|publisher=[[The Island (Sri Lanka)|The Island]]|date=16 June 2011}}</ref>
