'''SOCM''' stands for '''Statewide Organizing for Community eMpowerment''' (previously '''Save Our Cumberland Mountains''') and is a [[Tennessee]] community organizing group best known for its opposition to [[strip mining]]. It was founded in 1972 to oppose what the organization said were unfair imbalances in [[property taxes]], described by a group of [[Vanderbilt University]] students, between small and large landowners in the rural [[coal mining]] counties of [[East Tennessee]]. SOCM's focus later grew beyond the [[Cumberland Plateau]] and [[Cumberland Mountains]] regions, to include all of Tennessee. In 2008, SOCM changed its name from Save Our Cumberland Mountains to Statewide Organizing for Community eMpowerment to reflect its growing work in social, economic, and environmental justice. SOCM now has chapters in the cities of [[Jackson, Tennessee]] and [[Knoxville]], and [[Bedford County, Tennessee]], [[Maury County, Tennessee]], [[Rutherford County, Tennessee]] and [[Cumberland County, Tennessee]]. The Roaring River Chapter is made up of residents of [[Putnam County, Tennessee]], [[Jackson County, Tennessee]], and [[Overton County, Tennessee]].<ref>{{cite news|date=2003-03-17 |url=http://www.oakridger.com/stories/031703/stt_0317030022.html |title=Group continues to fight strip mining in Cumberland Mountains |publisher=The Associated Press |accessdate=2006-06-16 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071025004856/http://www.oakridger.com/stories/031703/stt_0317030022.html |archivedate=October 25, 2007 }}</ref>
[[J. W. Bradley]] of [[Petros, Tennessee]] is a cofounder and longtime leader of the group.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.socm.org/ | title = SOCM (Save Our Cumberland Mountains) | work = Official web site | publisher = SOCM | accessdate = 2006-06-16 }}</ref>
